Fairmont the Norfolk and Champagne house Moët & Chandon hosted guests to a tea party titled ‘The Champagne High Tea’ on February 28. High tea dates back to the 1700s in Britain and was created by Anna, Duchess of Bedford, to keep away mild hunger pangs in between meals. It later developed into a fashionable social event. The teme of the event was ‘Fifty shades of champagne’. In attendance were Bonfire Adventures MD Sarah Kabu, YouTuber The WaJesus Family and fashion and lifestyle blogger Lucia Musau among others.